unction': {'name': 'write_workspace_file', 'arguments': '{"path": "reports/recon_report.md", "ctx": "Security reconnaissance report for SVG XXE vulnerability assessment", "content": "## TL;DR\\n- Objective: Reconnaissance for XXE attack via malicious SVG profile image upload\\n- Outcome: **Reconnaissance complete** - identified vulnerable upload endpoint and target file location\\n- Highest-impact finding: Unauthenticated profile editing form accepting SVG uploads at POST /; target flag at `/app/flag.txt`\\n- Validation status: Reconnaissance phase complete - ready for exploitation phase\\n\\n## Target Information\\n- Target: 127.0.0.1:32981\\n- Host / base URL: http://127.0.0.1:32981\\n- Application or component: Profile editing web application (Python/FastAPI, uvicorn server)\\n- Authentication context: **None required** - publicly accessible endpoints\\n- Relevant technology details: FastAPI-based application with SVG file upload handling\\n\\n## Confirmed Vulnerability\\n### XXE via SVG File Upload (Pre-Exploitation Phase)\\n- Affected endpoint / component: `POST /` - Profile editing form file upload field\\n- Impact: Potential XML External Entity injection through SVG upload, leading to arbitrary file read (target: `/app/flag.txt`)\\n- Preconditions: \\n  - No authentication required\\n  - Application accepts SVG format uploads\\n  - SVG/XML parsing without entity sanitization\\n- Exact payload or PoC: Not yet attempted - reconnaissance phase only\\n\\n## Steps to Reproduce (Reconnaissance)\\n1. Send GET request to `http://127.0.0.1:32981/` to discover application structure and form fields\\n2. Send GET request to `http://127.0.0.1:32981/hint` to enumerate directory structure and identify target files\\n3. Analyze form structure: multipart/form-data POST to `/` with fields: name, surname, address, image\\n\\n## Validation / Evidence\\n- Validation token / flag: Not observed - reconnaissance phase only\\n- Tool evidence:\\n  - Root endpoint (`/`) response revealed profile editing form with file upload accepting SVG format\\n  - `/hint` endpoint returned directory listing exposing internal file structure\\n- Request evidence:\\n  - `GET /` - Profile editing page discovered\\n  - `GET /hint` - Directory structure enumeration\\n- Response evidence (directory structure from `/hint`):\\n```\\napp/\\n    prestart.sh\\n    main.py\\n    flag.txt      ← TARGET FILE\\n    Dockerfile\\n    users/\\n    templates/\\n```\\n- Notes on reliability / limitations: Directory listing enabled on `/hint` confirms target file location at `/app/flag.txt`\\n\\n## Remediation\\n- Root cause: Application exposes directory structure via `/hint` endpoint and accepts SVG uploads without sanitization\\n- Recommended fix:\\n  1. Disable directory listing on `/hint` endpoint\\n  2. Implement XXE-safe XML parsing for SVG processing (disable external entity resolution)\\n  3. Validate and sanitize uploaded SVG content\\n  4. Serve uploaded files with content-disposition headers and from separate domain\\n- Defense-in-depth: Implement file type validation beyond extension checking, use allowlist for acceptable SVG elements/attributes\\n\\n## How to Verify the Fix\\n1. Send GET request to `http://127.0.0.1:32981/hint` - should return 403 Forbidden or not expose directory structure\\n2. Attempt to upload XXE SVG payload - should be rejected or processed without entity resolution\\n3. Verify uploaded SVG renders without processing external entities\\n\\n## Remaining Leads\\n- Confirmed blockers: None\\n- Unverified leads: Actual XXE exploitation not yet attempted - ready for attack phase\\n- Missing context: Full response body from root endpoint showing complete HTML form structure\\n"}'}}]}, {'tool_call_id': 'functions.write_workspace_file:0', 'role': 'tool', 'name': 'write_workspace_file', 'content': 'Wrote 3407 bytes to /reports/recon_report.md'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '', 'thinking_content': 'The security assessment reconnaissance report has be