[32m│[0m ### detailed_summary                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Successfully exploited an XXE (XML External Entity) vulnerability on the     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m target web application. The application accepts SVG file uploads without     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m proper XML parsing restrictions, allowing external entity resolution.        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Vulnerability:** XML External Entity (XXE) Injection                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Attack Vector:** Malicious SVG file upload via multipart/form-data         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Target File:** `/app/flag.txt` (confirmed via previous /hint endpoint)     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Successful Exploitation Chain:**                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Crafted malicious SVG with external entity declaration pointing to        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `file:///app/flag.txt`                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Uploaded via POST to `/` endpoint with form fields (name, surname,        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m address, image)                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. Server resolved the entity and embedded file contents in response         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. Flag successfully extracted from SVG content in HTML response             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
